title: Penn State Event Network & Streaming Interface Design
description:
Engineered a theoretical network for a large-scale outdoor event using Cisco technologies and AWS, ensuring efficient,
secure live-streaming capabilities.
● Developed an interactive web interface with MERN stack, emphasizing user experience and security for real-time
event coverage and engagement

title: Penn State Foreign Terrorist Organization Report
description:
Collaborated with a team to produce a thorough analysis of a designated Foreign Terrorist Organization (FTO), and
created a comprehensive report covering origins, ideology, leadership dynamics, financial structures, strategic goals,
and historical case studies.
● Developed skills in research, analytical thinking, and strategic evaluation, contributing valuable insights into the
organization's impact on global security.
